    "about": {
        "headline": "I build <highlight>clean, scalable</highlight> products that feel <highlight>pixel-perfect</highlight> to use — and ship without drama.",
        "paragraphs": [
            "I'm <bold>Ricardo</bold>, a full-stack developer based in <bold>Asturias, Spain</bold>. I've spent the last few years translating designs into production-grade web apps, with a soft spot for the moments where engineering and craft meet — typography on a loading state, a transition that finally feels right, an API that reads like a sentence.",
            "I work most days in <bold>TypeScript</bold> on the React/Node side of the stack, with detours into Go when I need a CLI or a small service. I care about <bold>readable code</bold>, sensible defaults, and tools that disappear when they're working.",
            "Outside the editor I sit behind a <bold>drum kit</bold>. It's the best counterweight I've found to a job built on patience and precision — the same attention, just measured in milliseconds and groove instead of pixels and types."
        ],
        "philosophy": {
            "heading": "Jack of All Trades",
            "paragraph": "A jack of all trades is a master of none, but oftentimes better than a master of one."
        },
